Whether the budget will be lean and economical, which sectors will be preferred, which countries will be supported more and which less, all of this is on the agenda of the upcoming negotiations.
The ambassador also recalled her main slogans, with which she came to Brussels: "About Europe understandably."
“I really don’t like ugly abbreviations, foreign words, handicaps that no one understands.
How should the citizen understand that there are really no curved or round cucumbers in Brussels, bananas of varying sizes, or that we really have to be banned from cheeses.”
He also wants to make better use of the EU environment and get more Czechs into the European institutions.
