We try not to ride too much on tour because it’s very easy to fall into this trap of crowds and people who love our music.
When you realize that people came for music, you remind yourself that you must respect music and what you gave it. You must not be taken away by being famous rock stars.
What do you remember from Mother Love Bone?
I think we wrote great songs and in the beginning it was something spectacular.
We existed as a band for three years and never released an album until Andy (Andrew Woods) passed away.
It was very frustrating because it took so long. The most important thing is that today we are still friends with Bruce (Fairweather) and Greg (Gilmore), who started in a band with us. When I listen to a song or look at the photos, I remember Andy how incredible he was, how I laughed with him. It was always a pleasure to work with him, laugh, have fun with him about music or football and much more.
