The only one in Three Mile Island occurred under normal operating conditions and remained without human casualties and environmental consequences.
In Chernobyl, the drama was caused by the concept of the reactor and the inexcusable human error.
In the case of Fukushima, some seem to forget that the crash was the result of two natural disasters of unprecedented scale that caused the deaths of tens of thousands of people.
The nuclear industry will take lessons from this accident just as it did in the two previous ones.
The result of this step and the cooperation between French and German nuclear safety authorities, operators and engineers is that an EPR reactor represents a concept capable of resisting such phenomena.
